  relatedApplications={relatedApplications}
  relatedProducts={relatedProducts}
>

  <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-6 not-prose">
    <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed italic">Dolphin Centrifuge supplies disc stack centrifuge systems for machine coolant purification at 7,000+ Gs with separation to 1 micron. Systems from 3 to 50 GPM remove tramp oil, metal fines, and bacteria from water-based metalworking fluids. Based in Warren, Michigan.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-is-machining-coolant">What is Machining Coolant?</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-6 not-prose">
    <div class="md:w-[42%] shrink-0">
      <img
        src="/images/machine-coolant-centrifuge/machine-coolant-centrifuge-e1614448487484.webp"
        alt="machine coolant centrifuge"
        width="250" height="250"
        class="rounded-lg w-full h-auto"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="flex-1 min-w-0 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>Industrial operations with machining operations such as metal cutting, grinding, milling, etc., use coolants for product consistency and operational durability. Therefore the quality of the machining coolant is an essential factor for efficient machining operations.</p>
      <p>Many companies do not continually measure the contamination levels in their machining coolants. They have learned by trial and error that no problems will occur in the following machining stages by changing the coolant once a month or so.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Changing coolants just because they are dirty is an old-fashioned approach. It is also a messy and time-consuming task. With an industrial fluid centrifuge, you can control the contamination in the coolant tank.
  </p>

  <!-- ── Coolant Centrifuge ── -->
  <h2 id="coolant-centrifuge">Coolant Centrifuge</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-6 not-prose">
    <div class="flex-1 min-w-0 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>A machining coolant centrifuge is an industrial <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">disc centrifuge</a> that effectively removes tramp oil and sediment from the coolant continuously. It is a mechanical separator that uses centrifugal force to separate water-based coolants from denser metal particles.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="md:w-[42%] shrink-0">
      <img
        src="/images/machine-coolant-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-WSPX303-Coolant-Centrifuge.webp"
        alt="Alfa Laval WSPX303 Coolant Centrifuge"
        width="600" height="600"
        class="rounded-lg w-full h-auto"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <blockquote>
    Dolphin Centrifuge supplies turnkey coolant purification systems from 3 GPM for individual machines to 50 GPM for central coolant systems serving entire production lines.
  </blockquote>

  <!-- ── Operation ── -->
  <h2 id="operation">Coolant Centrifuge Operation</h2>

  <p>
    A machine coolant centrifuge exerts a very high centrifugal force of over <strong>7,000 Gs</strong> on the contaminated coolant. As a result, the small metal particles (down to <strong>1 micron</strong>) accumulate on the bowl wall from where they are self-ejected.
  </p>

  <p>
    The lighter coolant (free of contaminants) exits the centrifuge continuously through the fluid outlet passage.
  </p>

  <!-- Mid-Page CTA -->
  <div class="bg-navy rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 text-white mb-8 not-prose">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between gap-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Need Help With Your Coolant Purification System?</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-100">Our engineers will evaluate your machining coolant application and recommend the optimal centrifuge system.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="bg-gold hover:bg-yellow-500 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition whitespace-nowrap">Get a Quote</a>
        <a href="tel:+12485222573" class="border border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-navy font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition whitespace-nowrap">(248) 522-2573</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Advantages ── -->
  <h2 id="advantages">Advantages of a Coolant Centrifuge</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Savings:</strong> Centrifuge allows re-use of machining coolant.</li>
    <li><strong>Disposal:</strong> Recycling reduces disposal costs considerably.</li>
    <li><strong>Quality:</strong> Cleaner coolant leads to higher quality finished products.</li>
    <li><strong>Reliability:</strong> Contaminant removal leads to the durability of process equipment.</li>
    <li><strong>Health:</strong> Reduces bacterial contamination, which can cause health issues.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    In summary, an industrial fluid centrifuge offers several advantages, especially for the larger-scale handling of <a href="/cutting-oil-centrifuge/">cutting fluids</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-6 not-prose">
    <div class="md:w-[42%] shrink-0">
      <img
        src="/images/machine-coolant-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-Industrial-Centrifuge-Coolant-600.webp"
        alt="Alfa Laval Industrial Centrifuge Coolant"
        width="600" height="360"
        class="rounded-lg w-full h-auto"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Disadvantages ── -->
  <h2 id="disadvantages">Disadvantages</h2>

  <p>
    Despite the advantages listed above, there are certain disadvantages to centrifuges for coolant recycling. The following are some of the limitations of centrifuges.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Capital Cost:</strong> Coolant centrifuges are capital-intensive equipment. Though their payback period is relatively short, the initial cost can be daunting to first-time customers.</li>
    <li><strong>Sophisticated Construction:</strong> An industrial centrifuge is a high-speed machine with intricate moving parts. It is a mechanical separating machine that requires <a href="/industrial-disc-centrifuge-repair/">maintenance</a>. Comparatively, a filter is much simpler to operate than a centrifuge.</li>
    <li><strong>Auxiliary Utilities Needed:</strong> A <a href="/self-cleaning-disc-stack-centrifuge/">self-cleaning centrifuge</a> requires clean, potable water to operate the sludge ejection system. In addition, a centrifuge may also require compressed air (for sludge pumps). Filters don't need these additional utilities.</li>
  </ul>

