    <em>* Manual Clean = Operators need to stop and remove separated sludge. Self-Cleaning = Centrifuge automatically ejects separated sludge without stoppage.</em>
  </p>

  <!-- ── What is Tramp Oil ── -->
  <h2 id="what-is-tramp-oil">What is Tramp Oil?</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-6 not-prose">
    <div class="md:w-[42%] shrink-0">
      <img
        src="/images/machine-coolant-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-WSB-104-Concentrator-Coolant-Centrifuge-1000.webp"
        alt="Alfa Laval WSB-104 Concentrator Coolant Centrifuge"
        width="1000" height="545"
        class="rounded-lg w-full h-auto"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="flex-1 min-w-0 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>Water-based coolants get contaminated with oil from hydraulic machinery, metal coating, machine tools, etc. This oil accumulates in the coolant forming a floating layer known as tramp oil.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Problems associated with Tramp Oil ── -->
  <h3 id="tramp-oil-problems">Problems Associated with Tramp Oil</h3>

  <p>
    The following list of common problems associated with tramp oil in coolants.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Health Issues:</strong> Tramp oil floats on top of the water-based coolant, which causes anaerobic bacteria to grow. This bacterial growth is the cause of health issues such as dermatitis for machine operators.</li>
    <li><strong>Product Quality:</strong> When coolants are contaminated with tramp oil, they lose some of their lubrication and cooling properties.</li>
    <li><strong>Equipment Issues:</strong> Tramp oil causes reliability problems for auxiliary equipment that works with machine tools using coolants such as pumps, filters, etc.</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ── Tramp Oil Centrifuge ── -->
  <h2 id="tramp-oil-centrifuge">Tramp Oil Centrifuge</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-6 not-prose">
    <div class="md:w-[42%] shrink-0">
      <img
        src="/images/machine-coolant-centrifuge/water-based-machining-coolant-industrial-centrifuge-e1614449118510.webp"
        alt="water based machining coolant industrial centrifuge"
        width="250" height="250"
        class="rounded-lg w-full h-auto"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="flex-1 min-w-0 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>A <a href="/tramp-oil-centrifuge/">tramp oil centrifuge</a> is an industrial, 3-phase centrifuge designed to separate tramp oil from water-based coolants. It is a pass-through type of centrifuge that can separate the tramp oil from the coolants producing fresh, reusable machining coolant.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Tramp Oil Centrifuge Operation ── -->
  <h3 id="tramp-oil-operation">Tramp Oil Centrifuge Operation</h3>

  <p>
    A high-speed, disc-stack centrifuge produces over <strong>7,000</strong> gravity forces to continuously separate the tramp oil and solid particles from the machining coolant. The high g-force forces the heavy metal sediment to the bowl wall.
  </p>

  <p>
    It also concentrates the light tramp oil in the rotating bowl's center, which comes out of the center fluid passage; the clean coolant discharges through the outer fluid passage.
  </p>

